  rdfs:label "The first join goes from the baseline to the x-height line."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4771-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The dot for the letter i gets added once the letter string is complete."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.695240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8485-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that appears in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8485-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Themes in a story are used to convey deeper meaning and messages to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8485-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Readers can interpret themes and their importance in a story in different ways."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8485-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Don't Cross the Line!' explores the themes of authority, rule-breaking, identity and collaboration."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8485-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Stories can create a personal response linked to the reader's own views or personal experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-961-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "tion' is the most common spelling of /shun/."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-961-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Words ending in 'tion' are often nouns, like 'action', 'collection', 'question' and 'section'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-961-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: every and everybody."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700603Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5480-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every sentence must start with a capital letter and end with a full stop"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700608Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5480-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The beginning of a story introduces the main characters, setting and plot"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700613Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5480-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Word banks can be used to find key vocabulary or words that may be difficult to spell, such as 'cottage' or 'magical'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700619Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5480-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5480-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a sentence back after writing helps to check it makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700629Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6852-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Planet in a Pickle Jar’ is told through narrative writing and illustrations and it includes magical elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6852-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The grandchildren are characters and the narrators of the story which means it is told from their perspective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700656Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6852-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """At the beginning, the illustrations show a different story to the one being told by the narrators."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6852-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story contains multiple settings and it moves quickly between them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6852-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plot follows the grandchildren as they uncover their grandma’s desire to protect the world’s wonders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8131-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The colour blue is referred to repeatedly throughout the story and is part of what makes Asiya's hijab special to her."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8131-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The author states what the hijab isn't as a way of communicating its special nature."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8131-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Colours can be used to represent ideas, objects and feelings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8131-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Precise adjectives can enhance the description of colours and nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8131-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Similes can be used to compare two things using 'like' or 'as'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.700697Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8685-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Superheroes are fictional characters that have a special superpower"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703681Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8685-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Superheroes are often described as \"brave\", \"strong\" and \"powerful\""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8685-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Superheroes are known for wearing masks and capes"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8685-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Predictions can be made using the front cover, the title and information that we already know about the topic"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8685-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A front cover often reveals the title, author, illustrator and some illustrations"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7179-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One way of inferring a character's feelings is looking at their expressions in an illustration"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7179-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One way of inferring a character's feelings is reading about how they move, what they do and what they say"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703950Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7179-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Discussing the feelings of others helps to generate powerful adjectives to describe an emotion or event"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7179-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using 'I', 'me', 'my', 'we' or 'us' is a way of speaking in the first person"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.703959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6845-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adverbs can be used to describe how a character moves or speaks, such as "calmly"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6845-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sequencing language can be used at the start of a sentence, such as "Then," and "Suddenly,"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704043Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6845-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using the joining word \"and\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704048Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6845-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Exclamation marks can be used to show emotion, such as anger when the girl has a tantrum."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704052Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8690-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sentence is one idea that makes complete sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8690-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A space must be left in between each word so someone can read our writing"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704075Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8690-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sounding out a word before writing helps to spell a word"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704079Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8690-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8690-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sentence starts with a capital letter and mostly ends with a full stop"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8686-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most stories start by introducing the main characters and setting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8686-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plot means what happens in a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8686-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Illustrations are important to help to tell a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8686-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most stories explore a theme, which is a big idea"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8686-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Community, care and aspiration are themes that are explored in this story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704139Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8691-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes a noun, including ourselves, such as \"I am helpful.\""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704144Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8691-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives are describing words"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704148Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8691-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A person's character traits make that person who they are"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704153Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8691-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Someone's personality or character traits may be different to others'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704157Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8691-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Certain character traits are better suited to some jobs, such as bravery for a firefighter"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6204-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Information texts are a form of non-fiction writing that provide information about someone or something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6204-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of an information text is to provide true and factual information to inform the reader on a topic."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6204-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Information texts are written in the third person, using some second person to engage the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704195Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6204-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Headings and subheadings are key features that organise an information text into sections for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704200Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6204-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An information text about an author provides information about their life, e.g. childhood, inspiration, jobs and books."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704204Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5417-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading a story can help to summarise the plot and remember the main events"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5417-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme is a main idea in a story that often tries to teach the reader about something"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5417-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Relating the theme to ourselves can link the book to our own experiences"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704788Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5417-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Linking a story to our own experiences is thinking from our own perspective"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5417-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Responsibility means taking care of something, someone or completing some tasks"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8687-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Thinking from the character's point of view helps to understand events in the story"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8687-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading the story is useful to remembering the key events"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704992Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8687-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This story's plot is based around introducing different characters"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.704996Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8687-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Meeting these characters makes the reader reconsider what they define a 'superhero' as"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8687-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A job is what someone does for work"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705010Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8692-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing about what someone will be when they grow up means writing in the future, using phrases such as 'I want to...'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705060Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8692-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8692-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Common exception words are words that cannot be sounded out easily"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8692-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sounding out a word before writing helps to spell a word"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705074Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8692-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading back writing is important to check it is correct and makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705079Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8689-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes a noun, such as \"helpful nurse\""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705104Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8689-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives are describing words"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8689-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives can describe a person's appearance and personality"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705113Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8689-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A person's character traits make that person who they are"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8689-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Certain jobs require certain character traits, such as "patient", "caring" and "kind""""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705123Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6840-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Senses help us to experience and describe the setting, in this case, the forest."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6840-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The five senses are sight, smell, hearing, touch and taste."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6840-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An adjective or list of 2 adjectives can describe a noun, such as "wild forest" or "noisy, chirping birds"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6840-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using descriptions with adjectives makes writing more interesting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6840-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The joining word "and" can be used to join to complete ideas into a full sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.705284Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6844-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adverbs of time sequence events in the story, and can be used at the start of a sentence, such as "One day,"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6844-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adverbs of manner describe how characters move and speak, such as "roughly" or "weirdly"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6844-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Exclamation marks can be used to show expression and emotion, such as "I was fed up!"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706141Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6844-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing from the girl's perspective allows us to write about the girl's thoughts, such as "Where were we going?"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6844-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using the joining word \"and\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706150Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7174-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Recalling events in the story helps to summarise the most important parts"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7174-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The actions of a character are what the character does or says"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7174-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This story is different from traditional tales because it does not have a clear beginning, middle and end"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7174-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instead, this story follows each family member and the discussions that the main character has with them"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7174-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This story demonstrates there are different ways to show happiness and explores the themes of family and happiness"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6842-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling a story helps us to remember the main events in a story and think about the different parts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6842-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some events in a story can be joined using a joining \"and\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6842-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains map out the beginning, middle and end."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6842-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Powerful adjectives can be added to a story mountain, such as "ferocious", "vibrant" and "playful"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706263Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6842-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling the story in the first person means we have to imagine we are the main character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8688-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A noun is a naming word, such as a \"dentist\""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706557Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8688-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A noun is a person, place or thing"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706564Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8688-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a noun has a specific name of someone or something, it needs a capital letter, such as "Lily" or "England""""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706569Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8688-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sounding out a word before writing helps to spell a word"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706574Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8688-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading back writing is important to check it is correct and makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6197-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Non-chronological reports are non-fiction."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6197-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Non-chronological reports often have titles, subheadings and paragraphs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6197-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An introduction followed by two paragraphs of information is how we can structure a non-chronological report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6197-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-chronological report must be written in a formal tone, avoiding language choices associated with fiction writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6197-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Contractions are not used in formal writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6843-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This narrative is told in the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6843-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This narrative is written from the girl's perspective, using \"I\", \"me\" and \"my\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706874Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6843-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The beginning of a story introduces the main characters, setting and plot."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706879Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6843-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using a joining word \"and\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706883Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6843-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two adjective sentences describing characters and settings need a comma in between, such as "magical, dark forest"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9208-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And Tango Makes Three’ is a narrative fiction that is based on a true story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707054Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9208-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The main characters in the story are two boy penguins, one named Roy and one named Silo."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9208-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The story is set inside Central Park Zoo in New York City."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9208-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plot follows the story of how Roy and Silo find a way to become parents and have their own family."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9208-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Roy and Silo are the first family in the zoo to have two dads but they live and love just like all the other families."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5416-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character's facial expressions and actions help infer how they feel, such as when Lulu is told she can have a cat"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5416-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Asking questions to the character helps to consider key events and themes"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5416-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Illustrations can offer clues as to how characters might feel or what might happen next"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5416-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Thinking from a character's perspective helps us to understand the story better."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.707095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-980-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An adverbial complex sentence is formed of one main idea joined with subordination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-980-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Subordination joining words are 'because', 'so', 'when', 'if' and 'that'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-980-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adverbial complex sentence can be written in the past or present tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-979-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'So' and 'that' are types of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-979-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple sentence can be stretched with 'so' to give a result to the first idea."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-979-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simple sentence can be stretched with 'that' to give more detail about the first idea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-979-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joining the first idea with 'so' or 'that' forms a second idea that is subordinate to the first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-979-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using 'so' or 'that' to stretch a simple sentence forms an adverbial complex sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28998-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions must be followed in the correct order."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708893Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28998-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using numbers and sequencing language helps us to follow instructions in the correct order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28998-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The verb in the instruction tells us what to do, such as ‘slice’, ‘cut’ or ‘put’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28998-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Including adjectives in instructions can help us picture what we are going to be doing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5329-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing about what happened on a trip can come at the middle and end of a recount"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5329-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using time adverbials helps the reader to understand the sequence of events"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708919Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5329-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Expressing an opinion about the event can come at the end of the recount"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708924Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5329-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adding a 'Did you know...?' question at the end of a recount shows the reader what you learnt on the trip"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708929Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-908-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple sentence can be written in the past or present tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708933Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-908-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The tense of a simple sentence changes the time frame of the action."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708938Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27905-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful speaking includes speaking loudly and clearly enough for everyone to hear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708942Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27905-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful listening includes looking at the person speaking and paying close attention."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27905-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking in full sentences helps the listener understand what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27905-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Standing to speak helps to get the audience’s attention."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5196-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales try to teach us a lesson about something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708960Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5196-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Thinking about those lessons can help us change something in our lives."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708964Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5196-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Children of Lir teaches us to be resilient in the face of challenges."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5196-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sequencing events in a story means we put them in the order in which they happened."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5196-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sequencing key parts of the story helps to summarise the whole story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708978Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7196-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Performing poetry to an audience is an important part of the process of creating poetry."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7196-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When performing poetry, you must speak at a suitable volume."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708992Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7196-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using gestures and expression will make your performance fun and engaging for the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7196-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can improve our performances of poetry through practice."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709003Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5479-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An adjective describes a noun. Adjectives are often put in front of the noun in a sentence, such as 'green forest'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5479-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using descriptions with adjectives makes writing more interesting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5479-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Verbs are doing or being words"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709018Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5479-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Verbs are chosen carefully to help us imagine how someone has done something, such as “whizzed”"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5479-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can describe the appearance of someone or something as well as the personality of someone"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-909-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are four types of simple sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709712Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-909-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each type of simple sentence has a different purpose for the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709717Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-909-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Any simple sentence is a sentence about one idea that makes complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-909-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A statement is a simple sentence that expresses a fact or an opinion and ends with a full stop."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-909-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A question is a simple sentence that asks the reader for an answer and ends with a question mark."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8922-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One way of inferring a character's feelings is looking at their expressions in an illustration."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8922-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One way of inferring a character's feelings is reading about how they move, what they do and what they say."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8922-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagining how people might feel because of certain actions can help to understand the perspective of others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8922-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Discussing feelings of others helps to generate alternative & more powerful adjectives to describe an emotion or event."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709751Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8922-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using 'I', 'me' or 'my' is a way of speaking in the first person."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709755Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8926-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Senses help us to experience and describe the setting, in this case, London"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8926-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The five senses are sight, smell, hearing, touch and taste"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709764Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8926-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Expanded noun phrases need a comma in between the two adjectives, such as 'long, grand bridge'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709769Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8926-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sentence must include a verb"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709773Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8926-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using descriptions with adjectives make writing more interesting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8924-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A character's emotions can change at different points of the story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8924-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An emotion describes how someone is feeling."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709792Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8924-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Emotions can be different and shown in different ways, so descriptions must be chosen carefully."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709797Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8924-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Including a range of adjectives to describe the same feeling stops repetition and makes writing more interesting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8924-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you choose two adjectives to describe a noun, this is called an expanded noun phrase."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5434-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nouns can be written in a list using commas and 'and' used before the final noun, such as 'the coins, a hen and a harp.'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709815Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5434-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some adverbs describing how characters move can be used at the start of a sentence, such as 'Quickly,'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709820Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5434-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Exclamation marks can be used to show strong emotion, such as shock at finding an enormous beanstalk."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5434-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Powerful verbs can be used to describe what characters do, such as 'crept'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5434-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using a joining word, 'and'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.709834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8128-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that appears in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8128-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Themes in a story are used to convey deeper meaning and messages to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710220Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8128-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Proudest Blue' explores themes of identity, pride and differences, among many others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8128-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Stories can create a personal response linked to the reader's own views or personal experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8128-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Many different factors can contribute to a person's identity and everyone deserves to feel normal and proud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-905-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Verbs are doing and being words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710238Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-905-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Being verbs are \"is\", \"are\", \"was\" and \"were\"."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710242Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-905-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Verbs can be in different tenses."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-905-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A being verb can be the only verb in a complete sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-931-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘y’ is the most common representation of the 'igh' phoneme when it appears at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-931-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘i’ is a representation of the 'igh' phoneme found in the high frequency words: find, kind, mind, wild and behind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-931-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ie’ is a representation of the 'igh' phoneme found in the middle and end of words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.710997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-931-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: could, would and should."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6285-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presentations can be spoken aloud to an audience."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711006Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6285-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presentations are effective ways to share information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711011Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6285-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Presentations should be spoken clearly and at a suitable volume for the space you are in."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711015Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29000-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-reading what has been written so far will help to know what instruction will come next."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29000-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Each instruction should be numbered followed by sequencing language, such as ‘4. Finally,’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29000-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Each instruction should include a verb to tell the reader what they should be doing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29000-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Command sentences in non-urgent instruction pages start with a capital letter and end with a full stop."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711036Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29000-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reading your writing back and checking the success criteria helps to check that our writing makes sense"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27605-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful speaking includes speaking loudly and clearly enough for everyone to hear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711068Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27605-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking in full sentences helps the listener understand what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27605-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When retelling a story with someone, it is important to take turns and listen to what the other person is saying."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27605-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Storytelling language can help a listener to understand and enjoy a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711082Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-966-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-966-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding '-s' or '-es' to a noun creates a plural."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711091Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-966-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'y' is changed to 'i' before '-es' is added."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7197-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Magic Box’ by Kit Wright is a poem about putting a variety of unique and wonderful items into a special box."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7197-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use poems by other poets as inspiration for our own poetry."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711107Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7197-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The structure of a poem is how it is organised and put together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711112Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7197-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘The Magic Box’ is organised into verses that mostly follow the same structure."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7197-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Kit Wright is well-known for using contrasts in his poems."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7178-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Emotions can be different and shown in different ways, so descriptions must be chosen carefully"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7178-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An emotion describes how someone is feeling"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7178-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A character can feel different emotions at different points of a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7178-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Including a range of adjectives to describe the same feeling stops repetition and makes writing more interesting"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7178-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adverbs can be used to show how someone feels when they do something, such as 'counts quietly' or 'cartwheels happily'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-915-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And' is a type of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-915-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining two simple sentences with 'and' forms a compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-915-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The second idea builds on to the first idea if 'and' is used to join them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-915-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each of the two ideas holds equal grammatical weight in the sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-915-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences start with capital letters and most often end with full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711889Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27623-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A conversation is when two or more people take turns talking and listening to each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711894Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27623-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Listening when someone else is speaking is important in a conversation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27623-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sharing your opinion and explaining why you have that opinion is important in a conversation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27623-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Asking and answering questions are important parts of having a conversation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711937Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29017-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling a story helps us to remember the main events and use storytelling language, such as 'Once upon a time,'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711942Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29017-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains map out the beginning, middle and end of a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29017-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales often have repeated main events."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29017-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using sequencing language such as 'The next day,' at the start of the sentence helps the reader follow the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29017-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using descriptive language will make the story more interesting when writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.711963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5478-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagining you are the character helps to understand events and generate descriptions of the story"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716431Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5478-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Acting out stories helps to understand character's feelings and actions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716454Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5478-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By acting out parts of the story, vocabulary can be generated to help writing later"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5478-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Facial expressions and movements help the audience understand what is happening, such as shock from the girl"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716469Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5478-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Moving like the characters and objects can generate verbs, such as 'poured', 'raced' or 'hid'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716474Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-967-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-967-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'y' is changed to 'i' before '-es' is added."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-967-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Verbs agree with the noun they are paired with."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716487Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6211-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we are recounting, the information we are sharing with someone is called a recount."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6211-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount is written in the first person because it happened to you."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6211-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount is written in the past tense because the events have already happened."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6211-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount is written in chronological order."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716505Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-943-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'kn' can be a representation of the 'n' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716509Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-943-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The representation 'kn' is usually found at the start of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716514Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-943-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: push and pull."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716518Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-943-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Words connected in word families often have similar spellings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716524Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1057-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "er', 'ir' and 'ur' are common representations of the 'er' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1057-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: have, live and love."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-930-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘y’ is the most common representation of the 'igh' phoneme when it appears at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-930-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘i’ is a representation of the 'igh' phoneme found in the high frequency words: find, kind, mind, wild and behind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-930-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ie’ is a representation of the 'igh' phoneme found in the middle and end of words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-930-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: what, when and eye."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1056-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "er', 'ir' and 'ur' are common representations of the 'er' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716956Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1056-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: some and come."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716960Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1056-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A mnemonic can help us to remember tricky spellings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.716965Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1059-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """ear' is a representation of the 'er' phoneme that can ben found at the beginning or middle of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1059-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The 'or' representation of the 'er' phoneme is found after a 'w', such as 'word' and 'worm'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1059-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: friend."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1059-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Words in word families can have linked spelling, such as friend and friendly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-935-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "o' and 'oe' are representations of the 'oa' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717709Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-935-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘oe’ is a representation of the 'oa' phoneme most commonly found at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717716Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-935-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The 'o' representation of the 'oa' phoneme is in the high frequency words only, both and over."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-935-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: half and again."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7173-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making a prediction means making a guess about what you think will happen in a story using what you already know"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7173-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using illustrations, the title and knowledge that we already have helps us to make a prediction"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7173-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nigeria is a country in the continent of Africa"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717742Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7173-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Because Nigeria is close to the equator, it is a warm country"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717746Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7173-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "People can have different personal responses to what they have read"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717750Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8832-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is useful to pick out the important parts when retelling a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717755Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8832-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading a text helps to build fluency and understanding"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717759Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8832-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Searching for a \"word within a word\" is a strategy to understand words"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8832-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Retrieving key information helps to build greater understanding of a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717768Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28997-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions tell us how something should be done."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28997-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions are written as commands using verbs to tell us how something should be done."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717777Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28997-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions are often in a set order or sequence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717783Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28997-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions often have sequencing language and are numbered to help to follow the order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717787Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28997-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions may include pictures or diagrams to help to show what they do."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717792Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7214-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "John Foster is a poet and is known for writing humorous poetry for children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7214-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Foster’s poetry often explores everyday experiences that are familiar to children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7214-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Morning Rush’ is a poem about getting ready for school in the morning and how rushed the experience can be."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7214-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Repetition is used to create a sense of speed and urgency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717813Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5326-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Answering questions helps us to remember the details of the school trip"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717817Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5326-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Detail can be added to answers using descriptive adjectives and adverbs"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5326-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is important to share when and where the trip happened in a recount"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5326-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sharing why you went, how you travelled there and what you did adds additional information"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717833Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5326-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Noting down ideas and key words or phrases about the trip creates a plan for writing"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717837Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7195-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Mandy Coe is a poet and is known for writing imaginative poetry for children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7195-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘If You Could See Laughter’ by Mandy Coe is a poem about what laughter would look like if you could actually see it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717846Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7195-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem is imaginative and creates vivid imagery in the reader’s mind."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717851Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7195-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem explores themes of the joys of childhood and imagination."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7195-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can read with expression to convey a sense of fun and joy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-957-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ore’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that usually comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718169Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-957-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ough' and 'a' are alternative spellings of the 'or' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718174Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-957-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most words using the 'ough' spelling are past tense verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718178Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-957-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'or' sound is usually spelt as 'a' before 'l' or 'll'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-957-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: war, warm and towards."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718186Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-945-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'wr' can be a representation of the 'r' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-945-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The representation 'wr' is usually found at the start of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-945-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Words connected in word families often have similar spellings, such as write, wrote and written."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718202Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-945-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: ask and says."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8538-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Vocabulary in a story can generate a description of a character, such as the use of "stomping" and "destructive"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718211Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8538-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Descriptions of a character may change throughout the story as demonstrated through vocabulary, such as "lonely"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8538-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Powerful verbs and adjectives are used to help the reader build an image in their mind."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6171-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making any changes needed to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6171-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Punctuation is the name for the marks used to make our sentences clearer and easier to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6171-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we edit word choices, we carefully review and make changes to the words in our writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6178-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The purpose of the build-up is to develop the plot and characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718238Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6178-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time tell the reader how much time has passed between each sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718242Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6178-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Fronted adverbials of time can speed up or slow down the action being described."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718247Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6178-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use our plan to help form full sentences for writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-934-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'o' and 'oe' are rarer representations of the 'oa' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718696Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-934-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘oe’ is a representation of the 'oa' phoneme most commonly found at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-934-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: your and here."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-934-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Your' and 'you're' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718709Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-934-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Here' and 'hear' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718713Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-946-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'s' is the most common representation of the 's' phoneme at the start of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-946-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'c' is sometimes used to represent the 's' phoneme before 'i','e' or 'y'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-946-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "ss' is often used at the end of a word after a short vowel."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-946-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: path and bath."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.718753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-916-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'But' is a type of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-916-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining two simple sentences with 'but' forms a compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719054Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-916-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The two ideas in a compound sentence joined with 'but' oppose each other."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-916-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'but' joining word has a different meaning to the 'and' joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-916-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each of the two ideas holds equal grammatical weight in the sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6284-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A diary is an informal piece of writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719074Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6284-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One of the features of informal writing is contracted words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719079Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6284-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When writing informally, we use apostrophes for contraction to show two words connected together."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719083Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-926-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'e' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found in short high frequency words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-926-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'y' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-926-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'ey' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found at the end of a word, such as money."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-926-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'ie' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found in the middle of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-926-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: fast, last, past and plant."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-918-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining two simple sentences with 'and', 'but' or 'or' is called co-ordination."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-918-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And', 'but' and 'or' are three different co-ordinating conjunctions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719976Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-918-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A compound sentence is formed of at least two equal ideas and at least one co-ordinating conjunction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719980Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-918-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A compound sentence has at least two different verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6282-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Perspective is the way someone thinks, feels or sees something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6282-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing in a diary will mostly be in the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6282-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A diary entry should be written in the first person."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6282-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """First person is a point of view in writing or storytelling where the narrator or speaker refers to themselves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720004Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6170-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the climax is to describe the significant challenge and create the highest point of tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6170-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of manner tell the reader how something was done or how a character felt."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6170-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Rhetorical questions are questions addressed directly to the reader where an answer is not expected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720018Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5643-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions use a title to tell the reader what they are about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720022Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5643-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions can use an introduction to capture the reader’s interest."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5643-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Recipes can contain an ingredients list to tell the reader what they will need."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720034Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-911-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "And is a type of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-911-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A joining word can join two simple sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720045Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-911-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each simple sentence is about one idea and makes complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-911-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The second idea builds on to the first idea if ‘and’ is used to join them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720054Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-911-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences start with capital letters and most often end with full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720059Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29013-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There may be similarities and differences when comparing two traditional tales."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29013-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Thinking about characters, events in the plot and the setting can be helpful when comparing two traditional tales."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29013-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales often start by introducing the characters, such as seeing the three pigs leaving their homes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720072Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29013-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'The Three Little Pigs' teaches us about teamwork."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29013-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales mostly end happily, such as feeling safe and secure in your home with your family."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720080Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sitting position is important for handwriting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A comfortable pencil grip can make handwriting easier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It takes practice to be able to form a letter correctly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Handwriting patterns can help prepare to form letters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are some letter formations that require you to lift the pencil to add a dot or a cross."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8921-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea and focus of a book."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720900Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8921-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme in 'Paddington' and 'Coming to England' is identity as both books explore characters moving from their home."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8921-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Identity means who or what a person or thing is."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8921-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Someone's identity may include their background, personality traits and interests."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8921-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """How someone perceives their own identity is personal to them and may be different to how others perceive them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5652-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A subheading is a mini-heading given to a specific section of a report."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5652-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Fronted adverbials are sentence starters followed by a comma."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5652-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Great Fire of London started on Sunday 2nd September 1666."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720949Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5652-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire started in a bakery on Pudding Lane owned by Thomas Farriner."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5652-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire started from a spark in Thomas Farriner's oven."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720958Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-948-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letter 'j' is never used to represent the 'j' phoneme at the end of the word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-948-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'dge' is usually used after short vowels."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721037Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-948-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'ge' is usually used after consonants and other vowel sounds."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721041Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-948-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'g' is often used before 'i', 'e' and 'y'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721046Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-948-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: because."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4748-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sitting position is important for handwriting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721057Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4748-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A comfortable tripod pencil grip can make handwriting easier"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721062Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4748-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Handwriting patterns can help prepare us to form letters"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4748-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It takes practice to be able to form patterns correctly"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721071Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4748-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Posture, pencil grip and paper position are important for handwriting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721075Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6213-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount is written in the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721079Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6213-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A recount is written in chronological order and will use fronted adverbials of time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6213-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount is written in the first person."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721088Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8127-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We use a range of strategies to build comprehension of a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8127-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Skimming and scanning can help us to retrieve key information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8127-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use inference to draw conclusions about the text by searching for clues."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8127-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Discussing the text with others improves our understanding and offers opportunities for hearing different perspectives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721106Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8127-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Proudest Blue' challenges negative ideas around 'difference' and encourages pride of expressing religious identity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6179-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning is an important part of preparing to write."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721621Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6179-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The climax should be the most exciting part of the story for the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6179-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the climax is to describe the problem and create the highest point of tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6179-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using ambitious vocabulary helps to paint a vivid picture in the reader’s mind and make writing exciting to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6175-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The purpose of the opening is to introduce the main characters and the setting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721639Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6175-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning is an important part of preparing to write."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6175-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721648Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6175-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain nouns, adjectives, verbs and adverbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.721653Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-953-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ea' can be used to represent the 'e' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722292Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-953-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'tch' is the representation of 'ch' usually used after a short vowel."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722296Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-953-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exceptions to the 'tch' principle include the words: rich, which, much and such."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722301Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-953-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: any and many."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722306Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8209-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Robert Hull is a British writer who is mostly known for his stories, poetry and books written for children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722310Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8209-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Please do not feed the animals…’ is a humorous poem that reminds children of what not to feed the animals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722314Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8209-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This poem uses unexpected rhyming words at the end of each line to create humour."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722319Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8209-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we read aloud, we can use our voice to put emphasis on the rhyming words to convey the humour."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722323Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6165-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Creating a plan is a good way to help you prepare before completing a piece of writing"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722328Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6165-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plans will contain ambitious vocabulary"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722332Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6165-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two adjectives in an expanded noun phrase should be separated by a comma"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722336Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6165-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adverbs should be used to describe a verb"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722340Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5442-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Knowing the tune, words, rhythm and actions of a nursery rhyme makes it entertaining for the audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722345Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5442-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nursery rhymes follow either a rhythm or tune to keep to or in some nursery rhymes, both."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722349Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5442-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some nursery rhymes can be preferred by others compared to other nursery rhymes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5442-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Commenting on performances by highlighting what went well supports others to improve their performance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5442-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your personal response can be explained by using because."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6172-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An animated story is a narrative brought to life through the medium of animation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722369Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6172-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A question is a type of simple sentence that asks the reader for an answer and ends with a question mark."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722376Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6172-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questions start with question words and these need a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722380Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6172-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A question always ends with a question mark"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6172-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can ask questions about characters to help us engage with a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722389Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8109-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Things you think or believe are called your opinions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722394Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8109-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An audience is a group of people listening to or watching a performance or speaker"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8109-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking loudly and clearly is important when talking in front of an audience"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722419Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8529-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Texts often have a theme, or big idea, which is repeated through the story in different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8529-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme is a big idea or lesson that the author wants you to explore or understand."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8529-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In \"Grandad's Island\", the themes of family and separation are explored."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722639Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7217-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Home Time is a poem about the end of the school day."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7217-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Home Time is a poem written from the perspective of the classroom clock."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722648Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7217-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Home Time is a poem that uses personification."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722653Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7217-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Personification and perspective can be an imaginitive way to create humour."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722657Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8889-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Making a prediction means deciding what you think will happen next in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8889-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One person's prediction may be different to another person's."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722666Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8889-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Narrative openings introduce the characters, setting and plot."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722670Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8889-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Plop meets an old woman who likes the dark and says it is 'kind'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722677Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29016-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using 'I', 'me', 'my', 'we' or 'us' is a way of speaking in the first person."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722682Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29016-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """One way of inferring a character's feelings is looking at their expressions in an illustration."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722687Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29016-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Another way of inferring a character's feelings is reading about how they move, what they do and what they say."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29016-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Discussing the feelings of others helps to generate powerful adjectives to describe an emotion or event."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29016-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Considering an event in the story from a character's point of view helps us to understand the plot of the story better."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.722700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5435-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using a joining word, 'and'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724084Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5435-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Exclamation marks can be used to show surprise, such as when the giant follows Jack down the beanstalk."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5435-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some adverbs describing how characters may move can be used at the start of a sentence, such as 'quickly'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5435-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some adverbials of time build suspense, such as 'suddenly'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5435-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When we start a sentence with an adverb, we call it a fronted adverbial."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5412-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading key information can help to learn and remember it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724112Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5412-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Facts can be recalled from information in books."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5412-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A fact is a statement that is true, such as 'cats enjoy playing with toys'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5412-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Facts can be written in simple sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5412-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When listing what a cat needs, a comma must be placed between each noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5645-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making any changes needed to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5645-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Punctuation is the name for the marks used to make our sentences clearer and easier to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5645-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we edit word choices, we carefully review and make changes to the words in our writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724143Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27621-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Things you believe are called your opinions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27621-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "People can agree or disagree with an opinion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27621-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the word 'because' will allow you to explain why you agree or disagree with an opinion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27621-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking in full sentences helps the listener understand what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27621-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful listening includes looking at the person speaking and paying close attention."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724166Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-960-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "tion' is the most common spelling of /shun/."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-960-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: Monday."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-960-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Monday is a proper noun and is spelt using a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-960-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724184Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-932-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ow’ is a representation of the 'oa' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724367Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-932-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘o-e’ is a representation of the 'oa' phoneme that is often found 'last but one'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724371Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-932-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘oa’ is a representation of the 'oa' phoneme that is often found in the middle of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724375Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-932-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: who and how."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724380Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-962-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724384Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-962-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the suffix starts with a consonant letter, it is usually added without any change to the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724388Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-962-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a root word has more than one syllable and ends in a consonant + 'y', then 'y' is replaced by 'i' before the suffix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-962-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: whole."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724397Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5653-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A subheading is a mini-heading given to a paragraph within a main piece of writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5653-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Formal fronted adverbials link two sentences together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5653-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The second section of the report should inform the reader of how the fire spread and stopped."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-944-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'gn' can be a representation of the 'n' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724750Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-944-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The representation 'gn' is usually found at the start or end of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724754Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-944-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: school."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724759Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-944-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Words connected in word families often have similar spellings, such as sign and signal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724763Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1058-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'ear' is a representation of the 'er' phoneme that can ben found at the beginning or middle of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724768Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1058-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The 'or' representation of the 'er' phoneme is found after a 'w', such as 'word' and 'worm'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1058-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: said and were."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724779Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-2714-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe has more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724783Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-2714-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show contraction or possession."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724788Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-2714-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It's is the contracted form of 'it is' and does not show possession."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724794Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-2714-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Plural nouns that end in 's' do not use an apostrophe."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724799Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-963-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724803Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-963-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the suffix starts with a consonant letter, it is usually added without any change to the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724808Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-963-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a root word has more than one syllable and ends in a consonant + 'y', then 'y' is replaced by 'i' before the suffix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724812Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-963-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: beautiful."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724816Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-968-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-968-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding '-ing' creates an extra syllable to the word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-968-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'e', the 'e' is removed before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724829Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-968-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word has a short vowel and ends in a consonant, the consonant is doubled before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.724834Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-912-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A joining word can join two simple sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-912-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The second idea builds on to the first idea if 'and' is used to join them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725701Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-912-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining with 'and' is a type of co-ordination."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725705Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-912-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences start with capital letters and most often end with full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-912-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences do not have capital letters in the middle of them, except for proper nouns."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725714Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-925-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ee' and 'ea' are common spellings of the 'ee' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725937Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-925-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "e-e' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found 'last but one'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-925-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some words do not follow the rule, meaning they are an exception, such as 'even'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725946Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-925-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: door, floor and poor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1019-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe is an important piece of punctuation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1019-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe has more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725962Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1019-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another singular noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1019-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Apostrophes for singular possession are useful to make our writing clear."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1019-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe sits at the same height as the ascender of a letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6280-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A diary is a personal book where you write about your thoughts, feelings and experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725980Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6280-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Features are distinctive qualities or characteristics of something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725984Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6280-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The features of a diary entry include writing in the first person and past tense."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6280-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Diary entries usually include feelings and emotions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8482-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theme is a big idea or lesson that the author wants you to explore & understand through reading the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.725998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8482-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Readers can interpret themes and their importance within a story in different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8482-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Wolf, The Duck and The Mouse’ explores the themes of collaboration, optimism, and resourcefulness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726006Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8482-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Collaboration is the action of working with someone to achieve something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726011Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8482-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Collaboration is a skill that we learn and practise which has a variety of positive impacts on us."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726015Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-903-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One adjective can be used to describe a noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-903-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two adjectives can be used to describe a noun with more detail."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-903-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If two adjectives are used to describe a noun, they are listed with a comma."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-903-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A list of two adjectives followed by a noun is called an expanded noun phrase (ENP)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726034Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-955-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘aw’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word and sometimes in the middle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-955-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘oor’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that sometimes comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-955-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The proper noun 'August' is spelt using a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-955-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: busy, sure and sugar."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726443Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-929-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'igh' is a representation of the 'igh' phoneme that is often found in the middle of a word and 'loves a t'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-929-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘i-e’ is a representation of the ‘igh’ phoneme that is often found ‘last but one'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726454Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-929-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: there and where."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5432-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling a story helps us to remember the main events and use storytelling language, such as 'Once upon a time'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5432-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using storytelling language helps us to sequence events and provide a structure"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5432-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains map out the beginning, middle and end"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726472Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5432-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Powerful adjectives, verbs and adverbs can be added to a story mountain, such as 'enormous', 'crept', 'angrily'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726477Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5432-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains help to plan a story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5642-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imperative verbs make the instructions very similar to commands as they are bossy and tell the reader what to do."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5642-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions are written in chronological order and use ordering fronted adverbials to sequence them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5642-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A plan is written in note form and will help guide us when writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.726494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27906-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Standing to speak helps to get the audience's attention."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727431Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27906-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful speaking includes speaking loudly and clearly enough for everyone to hear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27906-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful listening includes looking at the person speaking and paying close attention."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27906-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking with volume helps to hold an audience's attention."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727447Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27906-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Actions and sound effects help add to a poem's meaning."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727451Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8904-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An aspiration is a hope or ambition of achieving something, such as what someone wants to be when they grow up"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8904-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To achieve an ambition or goal, a person must work for it and have certain character traits"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8904-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Someone's future ambition may be different to another person's and it is important to respect other people's opinions"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8904-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Certain character traits can be linked to specific ambitions or aspirations"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-981-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adverbial complex sentence is a main idea joined with a subordinate idea."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-981-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Subordination joining words are 'because', 'so', 'when', 'if' and 'that'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727757Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-981-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A compound sentence is a sentence formed of two main ideas and a joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-981-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Co-ordination joins two simple sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-981-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Co-ordination joining words are 'and', 'but' and 'or'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6166-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An opening will introduce the setting and main characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6166-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A descriptive opening will contain expanded noun phrases."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6166-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A descriptive opening will contain adverbs and verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727933Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6163-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A setting is where the story takes place."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727937Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6163-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two adjectives describing a noun is called an expanded noun phrase."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6163-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A comma should be used to separate adjectives in an expanded noun phrase."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6163-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use our senses to describe a setting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5436-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personal responses are a way of sharing your own thoughts, feelings and opinions about a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727957Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5436-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making connections between the text and your own experiences can help you make personal responses and draw conclusions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5436-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When making personal responses, it's important to support your opinions with evidence from the text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727966Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5436-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some people may believe Jack was the villain of the story for stealing and trespassing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727970Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5436-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some people may believe the giant was the villain for not sharing and for reacting in an angry, scary manner."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727974Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-937-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ew’ is a representation of the 'oo' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-937-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'oo' phoneme can be pronounced in two ways: 'oo' and 'yoo'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727983Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-937-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: put and Christmas."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.727988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6168-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the build-up is to develop the plot/characters, introduce a problem and build up tension and excitement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6168-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time tell the reader how much time has passed between each sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6168-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Fronted adverbials of time can speed up or slow down the action being described."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5640-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions are a set of steps or guidelines for someone to follow to complete a specific task."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5640-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions contain numbers or ordering fronted adverbials."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5640-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions contain imperative verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5640-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions contain adverbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5327-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Recounts are mostly told in chronological or time order"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5327-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Events in a trip can be placed on a timeline to help remember the sequence"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728177Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5327-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time such as 'First,' 'Then,' 'After that,' and 'Finally,' can be used to structure a recount"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5327-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Recounting orally helps to remember the events of a trip before writing"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728188Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8129-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The hijab is a very special item for the main character in 'The Proudest Blue'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8129-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can identify our own special belongings which hold meaning."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8129-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentimental items are ones that remind us of a special person, place, time or feeling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8129-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan is written in note format, using bullet points to write the key information in a few words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.728453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-939-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "ue', 'ui' and 'ou' are alternative spellings of the 'oo' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-939-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ue’ is a representation of the 'oo' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-939-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: move, prove and improve."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729281Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5415-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions can be added to an information report to tell someone what to do and how to do it, such as 'Feed your cat'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729285Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5415-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions can also be called commands as they are commanding someone to do something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5415-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions can also start with adverbials of time to sequence points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5415-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Limiting the amount of instructions or information can help the reader to understand more clearly."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729300Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5415-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adding photos or drawings can help the reader understand the information being given."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5195-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives that describe how someone is feeling help to read speech with expression."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729312Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5195-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adverbs may describe how a character has said something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5195-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Taking note of punctuation allows us to read with expression and communicate meaning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729321Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5195-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using different types of voice and different tones makes reading aloud more interesting for those who are listening."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729325Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5195-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You must decode and understand words to be able to add expression."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5149-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales often have a theme that is central to the story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729334Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5149-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The theme often leads to a moral that can teach us a lesson about something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5149-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Thinking about the moral can help us change something in our lives."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5149-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When we sequence events in a story, we put them in chronological order."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729347Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5149-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sequencing the main events of the story helps to summarise the whole story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729351Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8111-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An audience is a group of people listening or watching a performance or speaker"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729424Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8111-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An audience can be convinced to feel a certain way"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8111-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Convincing an audience requires strong reasons"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.729432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29015-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives can be used to describe the appearance of something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29015-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An appearance is what someone or something looks like, in this case what the houses looks like."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29015-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you use two adjectives to describe a noun, you need to separate them with a comma."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730113Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29015-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined together using 'and' to form one sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730117Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29015-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In a compound sentence, each idea must make complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8126-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Proudest Blue' is a children's picture book, written by Ibtihaj Muhammad, that celebrates being proud of the hijab."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8126-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The story is told from the perspective of Faiza and it is about her big sister Asiya getting her very first hijab."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8126-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sounding out using phonics strategies is our most helpful way to decode unfamiliar words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8126-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Searching for a 'word within a word' is a useful strategy to decode and comprehend words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8126-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-reading a sentence fluently after decoding helps to make meaning of what has been read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4746-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The numerals 0, 1, 2, 3 and 5 are formed using one contionous motion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4746-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The numeral 4 needs you to lift your pencil to add another line."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730151Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4746-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A numeral is a digit which represents a number."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730157Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8527-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """We can find out what a character is like in a variety of ways, including using the illustrations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730161Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8527-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The setting is where the story takes place, such as the island, or Grandad's house."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730165Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8527-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In this story the plot is developed through words and illustrations."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8527-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading aloud can help to bring the story alive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8527-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagining how a character is feeling helps us to think from their perspective, such as Syd feeling sad."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730181Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8903-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """a character description of yourself can be made about your personality and your appearance"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730185Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8903-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """describing your personality is about what you are like on the inside and how you feel, such as "curious", "resilient""""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8903-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """describing your appearance is about what you look like such as "curly, brown hair""""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730193Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8903-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """descriptions can create expanded noun phrases or be listed as nouns separated by a comma, like ‘socks, jumper and hat’"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8903-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """using verbs and adverbs can help to explain the adjectives you have chosen to describe yourself"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-949-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'dge' is usually used after short vowels."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-949-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'ge' is usually used after consonants and other vowel sounds."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-949-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'g' is often used before 'i', 'e' and 'y'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-949-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The spelling 'j' is usually used before 'a', 'o' and 'u'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-949-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: laugh."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7181-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A letter may include questions which you have to reply to."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7181-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Expanded noun phrases can help someone to imagine something or somewhere."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7181-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using two adjectives, a comma is placed in between them, such as 'fun, adventurous places'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7181-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adverbs can add detail to how someone does something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7181-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing in the first person uses words such as 'I', 'we' or 'mine'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730686Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8528-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Listening to and reading books is a way to learn new vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8528-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Powerful verbs are used to show how characters are speaking, such as "boomed" and "shouted"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8528-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use different strategies to work out the meaning of unknown words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8528-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading a story helps to develop our fluency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7218-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Allan Ahlberg is one of Britain’s most popular and successful children’s writers and is known for his fun storytelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730708Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7218-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Please Mrs Butler’ is a poem about a child asking their teacher for help."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730712Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7218-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Please Mrs Butler’ is written as a conversation between two characters and can be performed in a pair."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730716Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7218-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Performing a poem using expression and gestures will help to express to an audience how a character is feeling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730720Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6162-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Lucky Dip’ is an animated short story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6162-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘Lucky Dip’ is set at the seaside and takes place mostly in an old arcade."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6162-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sequencing means putting the events in the right order so they make sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6162-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Retell means to tell a story or explain something again in our own words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6162-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time tell the reader when the events in the sentence took place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.730741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-923-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'a', 'eigh' and 'ey' are alternative spellings for the 'ay' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-923-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Words in word families often have similar spellings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731202Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-923-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: great, break and steak."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-914-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exclamation is the fourth type of simple sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731211Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-914-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exclamation contains a verb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-914-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exclamation expresses strong emotion or surprise."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-914-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exclamation ends with an exclamation mark."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731223Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-914-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exclamation starts with 'What' or 'How'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731227Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8484-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Don't Cross the Line!' is a book that is mostly told through illustrations."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8484-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Layout refers to how the content is presented on the page."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8484-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The layout of 'Don't Cross the Line!' is a crucial part of telling the story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8484-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Stories that have few words are open to interpretation and designed to generate an opinion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8484-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can justify an interpretation or opinion by offering a clear reason or explanation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731248Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6201-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning is an important part of preparing to write."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731252Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6201-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan helps a writer to organise their ideas, thoughts and the information they want to include in their writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6201-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes can be used in a plan to help organise key information and are not written in full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6201-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hedgehogs are nocturnal animals, which means they sleep during the day and are awake at night."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6201-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hedgehogs have thousands of spines that they use to protect themselves from predators."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731271Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6202-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Compound sentences are sentences formed of two simple sentences and a joining word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6202-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Co-ordination means joining two simple sentences with 'and', 'but' or 'or'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6202-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A joining word is a word that joins words or ideas."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731286Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6202-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The second section of the report will be all about hedgehogs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6829-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731295Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6829-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a sentence back after writing helps to check it makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731299Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6829-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every sentence must start with a capital letter and end with a full stop"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6829-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales tend to end with a happy ending"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731308Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6829-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Word banks help to find keywords to include in writing"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.731312Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8928-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adding descriptive language to a postcard helps the reader imagine what the place is like."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8928-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two adjective sentences need a comma in between the two adjectives, such as 'black, zooming taxi'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8928-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Asking a 'Did you know ...?' question teaches someone a fact about something, in this case, London."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8928-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A postcard should end with naming who the postcard is from, in this case, Paddington."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-965-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732017Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-965-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the suffix starts with a consonant letter, it is usually added without any change to the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-965-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a root word has more than one syllable and ends in a consonant + 'y', then 'y' is replaced by 'i' before the suffix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6823-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales are stories that are retold again and again and can be retold in different ways"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732057Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6823-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales often have heroes, such as the goats and villains, such as the troll"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6823-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most traditional tales start by introducing the characters and the settings"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732069Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6823-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales have lots of similarities"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6823-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Usually, a problem is solved by the end of the story"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6824-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling a story helps us to remember main events in a story and use storytelling language, such as 'Once upon a time'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732083Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6824-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains sequence the beginning, middle and end of a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732087Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6824-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Only the most important events in the story need to be on a story mountain."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732091Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6824-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using words such as 'First,' and 'The next day,' at the start of the sentence helps the reader follow the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6824-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains can be used to retell the story aloud."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6186-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A complex sentence is a sentence formed of a simple sentence joined with subordination."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732634Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6186-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Subordination means joining a simple sentence with a second idea of lower importance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6186-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Mary Seacole was a doctress who helped injured soldiers during the Crimean war."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732644Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6186-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Mary set up her own hospital in Crimea called the British Hotel."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732648Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8264-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-reading a story helps to build deeper understanding and identify underlying themes and messages."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8264-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that appears within a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8264-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In "Leaf", the themes of belonging, kindness, environment and climate change are explored."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8264-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A sense of belonging is essential for the survival of all living things."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8264-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Leaf may help the reader to reflect on respect for the environment and how to support others' sense of belonging."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732670Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5651-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan helps a writer to organise their ideas, thoughts and the information they want to include in their writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5651-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The fire started on Sunday 2nd September 1666 in a bakery on Pudding Lane in London."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732678Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5651-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire was accidentally started by a baker named Thomas Farriner."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732682Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5651-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes can be used in a plan to help organise key information and are not written in full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732686Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29020-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales often end happily by finding a solution to a problem."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732690Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29020-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using adjectives, like ‘scorching’, and powerful verbs, like ‘plunged’, help the reader picture the events of a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29020-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Exclamation marks can help to express a feeling of shock or surprise."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29020-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The sequencing word ‘Suddenly,’ helps to sequence events and to show something sudden has happened."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732706Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-902-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives are words that can compare nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-902-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing nouns is another way to describe them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-902-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives most often compare common nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.732718Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8125-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The author of 'The Proudest Blue' is Ibtihaj Muhammad, written alongside S. K. Ali."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733552Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8125-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Proudest Blue' is a children's picture book which celebrates the importance and beauty of the hijab."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733558Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8125-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'The Proudest Blue' is inspired by the author's own life."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733562Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8125-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Ibtihaj Muhammad was the first American fencing player to wear the hijab and participate in the Olympics."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733566Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8125-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Ibtihaj wrote 'The Proudest Blue' so that young girls who wear the hijab can see themselves represented and feel proud."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733570Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8265-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Planet in a Pickle Jar’ contains precise vocabulary that is crucial for understanding the meaning behind the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733574Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8265-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The grandma describes the planet as “fragile” and wants to “preserve” it so she creates a “sanctuary”."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733578Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8265-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Special things are pickled in jars because pickling is a method of preservation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733582Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8265-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The story explores the preservation of the world’s natural elements, human elements and items/belongings."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733586Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8265-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The illustrations communicate additional meaning behind the vocabulary in the story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5482-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The last sequencing word used should show the story is coming to a close, such as 'Last,' or 'Finally,'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5482-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The ending of a story usually solves the problem and ends happily."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5482-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5482-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a sentence back after writing helps to check it makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5482-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Every sentence must start with a capital letter and end with a full stop (or other closing punctuation)"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733611Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5647-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The Great Fire of London happened in the past."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733618Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5647-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire started on Sunday 2nd September 1666."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5647-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire started in Pudding Lane in Thomas Farriner’s bakery."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5647-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The fire spread quickly due to the houses being made of wood, being close together and the windy conditions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5647-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire lasted for four days before it was stopped."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733634Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6203-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presentations can be spoken aloud to an audience."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6203-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Presentations are effective ways to share information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733641Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6203-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Presentations should be spoken clearly and at a suitable volume for the space you are in."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733645Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5429-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe a character's appearance and personality, such as 'enormous, greedy' giant."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5429-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using two adjectives, a comma is placed in between them, such as 'the enormous, greedy giant'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733653Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5429-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined together using 'and' to form one sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733657Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5429-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using 'and' connects two ideas together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733661Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5429-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Referring to the giant as 'he' after naming him makes writing less repetitive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733665Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-938-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ue’ is a representation of the 'oo' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733671Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-938-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "ue', 'ui' and 'ou' are alternative spellings of the 'oo' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-938-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: many and after."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8173-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the introduction is to engage the reader, introduce the author and provide general information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8173-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An information text begins with a heading about the whole text and a subheading for the introduction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8173-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are four main sentence types (a statement, a question, a command and an exclamation)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8173-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a variety of sentence types in your introduction helps to engage and inform the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733877Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8173-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The text is mainly written in third person to inform the reader, with the use of some second person to engage them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733881Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-919-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And', 'but' and 'or' are three different co-ordinating conjunctions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733887Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-919-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The co-ordinating conjunction used changes the meaning of the compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-919-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Co-ordination helps our writing flow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733895Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6187-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Comparing means looking at how things are the same and contrasting means looking at how things are different."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6187-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The purpose of the conclusion is to summarise the information from the report."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6187-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "No new information is given in the conclusion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5414-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An information page needs to be easy to read and understand."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5414-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An information page needs a title such as 'How to look after cats'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5414-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An information page needs to include subject-specific vocabulary such as 'shelter' or 'healthy'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733921Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5414-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When listing what a cat needs, a comma must be placed between each noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733924Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5414-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Fun Facts' or 'Did you know?' questions can be added to make the writing more interesting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733928Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5440-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Five Little Ducks Went Swimming One Day' has some rhyming words, such as 'day' and 'away'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733932Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5440-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Knowing the tune, words, rhythm and actions of a nursery rhyme makes it more entertaining for an audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5440-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Hickory Dickory Dock' and 'Five Little Ducks Went Swimming One Day' are similar because they both include counting."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5440-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personal responses are a way of sharing your own thoughts, feelings, and opinions about a poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733943Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5438-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nursery rhymes are aimed at children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5438-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nursery rhymes might have words that rhyme in them, which are words that end in the same sound or sounds."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733953Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5438-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nursery rhymes are often sung in a tune."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733957Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5438-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nursery rhymes are often easy to learn and have repeated elements or refrains."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5438-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nursery rhymes often link to historical events or periods."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733965Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-969-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-969-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The past tense of some verbs may sound like they end in 'id', 't' or 'd', but they are spelt using '-ed'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-969-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the verb ends in two consonant letters, the ending is simply added on."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-969-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the verb ends in a consonant + 'y', the 'y' is changed to 'i' before 'ed' is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733983Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-969-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'e', the 'e' is removed before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5197-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Looking out for clues in the text and illustrations can help answer questions that may not have obvious answers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5197-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Inference skills can help to develop a deeper understanding of a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.733997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5197-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An opinion is a view about something, somewhere or someone that is personal."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5197-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One person’s opinion can differ from someone else’s opinion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5197-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Opinions should be able to be justified or explained in a respectful way."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8481-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The author’s choice of vocabulary is precise and ambitious and is used to convey meaning to the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8481-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Repetition of keywords can enhance and support storytelling."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734017Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8481-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Multiple words can be used to describe the same thing, e.g. “gobbled”, “munched” and “feasted”."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8481-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Character speech is used to show the perspective and feelings of different characters and this impacts how it is read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8481-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Summarising a story helps us to build our understanding of a text and the meaning behind it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28999-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Rehearsing what we want to write aloud helps us to hold the information in our head."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28999-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions start with a title, such as ‘How to make a sandwich’."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28999-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions often include a list of what you will need, in this case, ingredients."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28999-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A list might be put into a sentence or written as listed objects on separate lines."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5430-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe a character's appearance and personality, such as 'small, sneaky Jack'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5430-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using two adjectives, a comma is placed in between them, such as 'small, sneaky Jack'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5430-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined together using 'and' to form one sentence"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734386Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5430-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using 'and' connects two ideas together"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5430-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Referring to Jack as 'he' after naming him makes writing less repetitive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734394Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6164-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective is a word that describes a noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734398Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6164-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two adjectives describing a noun is called an expanded noun phrase."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6164-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A comma should be used to separate adjectives in an expanded noun phrase."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6164-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character is a person or animal in a fictional story. They are not real and have been created by the writer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734410Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5328-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing about when and where the trip was should come at the beginning of a recount"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734414Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5328-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Explaining why the trip happened can come at the beginning of a recount"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5328-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Explaining how you travelled to the trip can come at the beginning of a recount"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5328-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding interesting adjectives and adverbs makes a recount more interesting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5328-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two events in a recount can be joined together using the joining word, 'and'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.734429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8902-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A character description can be generated using evidence from the text"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8902-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We know that Ada is curious because she asks lots of questions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8902-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives can be used to describe a character"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735262Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8902-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two similar ideas can be joined together using 'and'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735266Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8902-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Because' can be used to explain your ideas"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7177-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Senses can be used to describe and imagine a setting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7177-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using two adjectives, a comma is placed in between them, such as 'warm, vibrant Nigeria'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735475Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7177-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes a noun"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7177-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we place more than one noun before an adjective, it is called an expanded noun phrase"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28996-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A design is a drawn and labelled plan for what something is intended to look like when complete."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735489Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28996-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A design includes labels and captions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735493Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28996-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A design includes what materials or things you will need to make it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735497Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28996-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A noun is a naming word for a person, place or thing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-28996-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes or adds detail to a noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6181-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Editing is the process of making any changes needed to improve our writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6181-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Punctuation is the name for the marks used to make our sentences clearer and easier to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6181-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When we edit word choices, we carefully review and make changes to the words in our writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6181-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our choice of adjectives, adverbs and verbs should be precise and descriptive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735520Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5146-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Proper nouns have capital letters and can involve more decoding skills than understanding skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735524Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5146-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sounding out using phonics strategies is our most helpful way to decode unfamiliar words, such as "whispered"."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5146-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Common exception words are important to learn and remember, such as 'said'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735531Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5146-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Re-reading a sentence can help us make sense of it and ensure understanding."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5146-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Looking at the illustrations can support comprehension."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.735539Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5431-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Expressions and actions of characters help us to infer how a character feels, such as when Jack races up the beanstalk"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736342Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5431-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Recalling parts of a story help us to remember what happened, such as remembering the order of what Jack steals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736346Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5431-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Asking questions to the character helps us to consider key events and themes"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736350Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5431-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Illustrations can offer clues as to how characters might feel or what might happen next"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736354Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5431-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Thinking from different character's perspectives helps us to decide which character is in the right or wrong"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736358Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8130-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Notes from a written plan support in writing a sequence of senences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736362Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8130-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Co-ordination can be used to join two simple sentences that carry equal importance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8130-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Subordination can be used to stretch a main clause and explain ideas to the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8130-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials followed by a comma can be used to sequence sentences and add detail to the main clause."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-977-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Because' is a joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-977-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simple sentence can be stretched with 'because' to give a reason to the first idea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736418Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-977-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joining the first idea with 'because' forms a second idea that is subordinate to the first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736422Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-977-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using 'because' to stretch a simple sentence forms an adverbial complex sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7182-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A letter may include questions which you have to reply to"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736430Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7182-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A further question might be asked at the end of the letter so someone can reply"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7182-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questions must end in a question mark"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7182-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A question is a type of simple sentence that asks someone for an answer"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7182-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Letters need to end with a closing and the writer's name so the reader knows who the letter is from"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1018-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe is an important piece of punctuation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1018-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe has more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1018-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can contract two words together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736457Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1018-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Apostrophes for contraction are useful in informal writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1018-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe sits at the same height as the ascender of a letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6205-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An information text about an author provides information about their life, e.g. childhood, inspiration, jobs and books."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6205-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Atinuke is a Nigerian born author whose stories are inspired by African culture and traditional storytelling."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736475Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6205-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Roald Dahl was a British author who wrote popular children’s literature containing imaginative and magical elements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736479Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6205-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Ibtihaj Muhammad is an American fencer and author who was inspired to write stories celebrating the Muslim identity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736483Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6205-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Developing a personal response to what we have read can inspire in writing our own information text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736488Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27775-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A numeral is a digit that represents a number."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27775-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The numerals 6, 7, 8 and 9 are made using one continuous movement and without lifting your pencil."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27775-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The formation of the numeral 10 requires you to lift your pencil as it has two separate digits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27775-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The numerals 6 to 10 all sit on the baseline."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5646-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Non-chronological reports are non-fiction."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5646-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Non-chronological reports often have titles, subheadings and paragraphs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736514Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5646-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An introduction followed by two paragraphs of information is how we can structure a non-chronological report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736518Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5650-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A question to the reader should end with a question mark."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736524Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5650-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using interesting general facts can gain the reader’s interest and make them want to read the full report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5650-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A command should start with an imperative verb and entice the reader to read on."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.736532Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8132-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading aloud is a way to present your writing to an audience."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8132-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Volume, eye contact, body language and pace are important for connecting to the audience effectively."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8132-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Style of presentation is impacted by what you are reading aloud."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737213Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8132-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personal writing should be delivered in an expressive and emotive way using emphasis where appropriate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8132-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing reading aloud helps to prepare us for presenting."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737220Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7215-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Performing poetry can be an effective way to bring a poem to life for an audience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737404Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7215-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Physical gestures and actions help to make a poem more engaging to watch."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7215-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can improve our performances of poetry through practice."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7215-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Varying the volume and tone of your voice when performing a poem can make a poem more engaging to listen to."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5413-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions or commands tell someone what to do."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737419Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5413-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Giving an instruction to someone can be useful in teaching them something or giving them information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5413-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions mostly start with verbs, such as 'feed your cat twice a day' or 'give your cat a bowl of water'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5413-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions can come in a sequence using sequencing language, such as 'First, put a bed down for your cat.'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737433Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5413-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A command can include a list, such as 'Give your cat water, food and love.'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737437Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-972-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-972-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word has a short vowel and a single consonant, the consonant letter is doubled when the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-972-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letter 'x' is never doubled, such as words like mixing, mixed or boxer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5147-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Taking note of punctuation allows us to read with expression."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5147-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different punctuation marks mean different things."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737456Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5147-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-reading words that you have read before gives you a chance to concentrate on reading with expression."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737460Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5147-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using different types of voice and different tones makes reading aloud more interesting for those who are listening."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737464Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5147-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You must decode and understand words to be able to add expression."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737468Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6209-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes from a written plan support in writing and ensure important information is included in an information text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6209-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using a range of sentence types (simple, compound and complex) in our writing helps it to flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6209-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials are sentence starters followed by a comma and they support text flow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737687Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6209-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Viewpoint fronted adverbials express the writer’s opinion and fronted adverbials of time state when something happened."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737691Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6195-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Bats are nocturnal animals, which means they sleep during the day and are awake at night."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6195-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Bats have very poor eyesight, but use echolocation to help them navigate their way around."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6195-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Bats have leathery wings which help them to fly quickly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6195-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Over millions of years, bats have developed adaptations to help them survive."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737707Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-971-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-971-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the adjective ends in two consonant letters, the ending is simply added on."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-971-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'y', the 'y' is changed to 'i' before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737718Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-971-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'e', the 'e' is removed before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5475-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Predictions can be made based on illustrations, what has already been read and the front cover"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737729Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5475-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One person's prediction may be different to another person's"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5475-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales often start by introducing the characters, such as the little girl and setting the scene"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5475-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'The Magic Porridge Pot' teaches us to be generous and helpful to others"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5475-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales mostly end happily, such as having enough food and sharing with others"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.737744Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-956-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ore’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that usually comes at the end of a word, such as more."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.738851Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-956-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ough' and 'a' are alternative spellings of the 'or' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.738855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-956-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'or' phoneme is usually spelt as 'a' before 'l' or 'll'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.738859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-956-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most words using the 'ough' spelling are past tense verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.738863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-956-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: water, always, walk and talk."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.738867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6180-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The climax should be the most exciting part of a story for the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739178Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6180-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two simple sentences joined together with a joining word is called a compound sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6180-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use our plan to help form full sentences for writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739186Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6180-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of manner tell the reader how something was done or how a character felt."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739190Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6180-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adverbs are words that describe a verb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5476-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing means exploring similarities and differences about something"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5476-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Characters, such as heroes and villains, tend to appear in most fairy tales"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739202Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5476-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some fairy tales' main characters are people and some are animals"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5476-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Some fairy tales have magical aspects or creatures, such as the porridge pot or the troll"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739212Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5476-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Most fairy tales aim to teach a lesson to the reader"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739216Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5428-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales are stories that are retold again and again and can be retold in different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739561Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5428-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some traditional tales have magical aspects such as magic beans or beanstalks."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5428-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales try to teach us a lesson about something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739569Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5428-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales often have heroes and villains."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739573Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5428-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Jack could be described as the hero or the villain from different perspectives."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6828-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739584Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6828-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a sentence back after writing helps to check it makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739588Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6828-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every sentence must start with a capital letter and end with a full stop"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739591Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6828-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Narrating a story means the writer is saying what happens"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6828-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Word banks help to find keywords to include in writing"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.739601Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-942-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "mb' can be a representation of the 'm' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740061Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-942-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The representation 'mb' is often found at the end of a word, such as climb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-942-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word: parents."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740069Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-974-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Compound words are two or more words joined together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-974-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In a compound word, the spelling of the original words stays the same."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-974-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Football', 'notebook', 'inside' and 'sometimes' are all compound words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.740105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5148-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Summarising what we have read can help us to remember and understand a story better."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741254Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5148-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Skimming and scanning using your finger is a way to retrieve information quickly and accurately from a text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741258Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5148-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Searching for capital letters helps us to find proper nouns quickly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741266Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5148-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Searching for keywords can help us find answers quickly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5148-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Responding to texts with discussions can help to deepen our understanding."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741274Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6169-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the climax is to describe the problem and create the highest point of tension."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741888Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6169-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6169-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain nouns, adjectives, verbs and adverbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6169-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using ambitious vocabulary helps to paint a vivid picture in the reader’s mind and make writing exciting to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741902Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6173-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sequencing means putting the events in the right order so they make sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6173-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Otherwise’ is an animation which follows Anders, a red chameleon, who is different to the others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6173-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Retell means to summarise a story in your own words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6173-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Fronted adverbials of time tell the reader when the events in the sentence took place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8918-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Stories have a beginning, middle and end."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8918-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Paddington book series is now also told through film and television programmes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741926Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8918-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Paddington is a a fictional story set in London."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741930Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8918-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """People may have different responses to a story, such as their favourite part and favourite character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.741934Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5649-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The introduction of an information text should hook the reader in and make them want to read the full report."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742591Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5649-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Introductions often contain questions to the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742595Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5649-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An introduction may contain some general facts and information to gain the reader’s interest."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742599Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5649-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An introduction may end with a command which is a direct order or instruction telling the reader to continue reading."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742603Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8272-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Rachel Rooney is a poet and is known for writing imaginative poetry for children."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742607Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8272-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘Wide Open’ by Rachel Rooney is a poem about a special eye that can see anything."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742611Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8272-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem is imaginative and has themes of wonder and discovery."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8272-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The poem explores themes of imagination, wonder and discovery."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.742619Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6825-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Imagining you are the character helps to understand events and generate descriptions of the story"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743012Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6825-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Describing how a character is looking or what they are doing helps us to understand the plot of a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6825-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Facial expressions and movements help the audience understand what is happening, such as fear from the goat"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6825-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are different ways to express emotions. Facial expressions and actions help us to show feelings and emotions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6825-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The feelings we have can result in actions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743028Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5654-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The fire spread quickly because the weather was dry, hot and windy."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743032Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5654-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There was no fire brigade so Londoners used leather buckets, axes and water squirts to try and fight the fire."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5654-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A plan helps a writer to organise their ideas, thoughts and the information they want to include in their writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743042Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5654-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes can be used in a plan to help organise key information and are not written in full sentences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743046Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27908-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Things you like or dislike are called your 'opinions'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743052Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27908-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "People can agree or disagree with an opinion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743056Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27908-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the word 'because' will allow you to explain why you like or dislike something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743060Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27908-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking in full sentences helps the listener understand what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27908-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful speaking includes speaking loudly and clearly enough for everyone to hear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743069Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4749-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Pre-cursive letters all start on the baseline with a lead in"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4749-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters i, l and t all have a lead in and a lead out"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743077Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4749-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We remember where to start by saying 'Ready, line, go'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743081Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4749-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters i, l and t are all formed by going up and then down"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6177-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning is an important part of preparing to write."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6177-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the build-up of a story is to develop the plot and characters and introduce a problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6177-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6177-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain nouns, adjectives, verbs and adverbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8831-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A biography is a non-fiction text"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743196Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8831-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A biography tells the true story of a person's life"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743199Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8831-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Biographies are written in chronological order"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743203Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8831-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Biographies are often written about significant figures"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743207Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8831-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Emmeline Pankhurst was a significant historical figure"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743211Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29018-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales are mostly told in the past tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29018-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The beginning of a story introduces the main characters, setting and plot."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29018-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined using the joining word 'and'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29018-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When a sentence has two adjectives before a noun, a comma is needed between them, such as 'excited, adventurous pigs'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29018-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An adverb describes a verb; adverbs can describe how something happened, such as ‘proudly’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-978-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'When' and 'if' are types of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-978-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simple sentence can be stretched with 'when' to give a time frame to the first idea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743311Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-978-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A simple sentence can be stretched with 'if' to give conditions to the first idea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743315Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-978-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Joining the first idea with 'when' or 'if' forms a second idea that is subordinate to the first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743321Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-978-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using 'when' or 'if' to stretch a simple sentence forms an adverbial complex sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743325Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9209-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A theme is a big idea, topic or message that appears in a story."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9209-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And Tango Makes Three' tells the story of a penguin family that has two dads."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9209-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'And Tango Makes Three' explores themes of love, family and identity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9209-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Families come in many different forms, shapes and sizes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743378Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-9209-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Love is the most important element in a family."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-964-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743386Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-964-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the suffix starts with a consonant letter, it is usually added without any change to the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-964-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a root word has more than one syllable and ends in a consonant + 'y', then 'y' is replaced by 'i' before the suffix."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6208-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The subheading ‘Jobs and books’ tells the reader what the section will be about."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6208-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plan should include any other jobs the author had and their journey to becoming an author in chronological order."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743751Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6208-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The plan should include a piece of current information about the author or other books by them to end the section."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6208-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are used when making a plan and capture key vocabulary and important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6208-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are not written in full sentences and do not require capital letters or full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743764Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-973-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A prefix is a letter or group of letters at the start of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743768Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-973-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The prefix 'un-' is added to the beginning of a word without changing the spelling of the root word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743772Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-973-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The prefix 'un-' usually means not."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743778Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-899-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Nouns are words that name people, places or things."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743782Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-899-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Common nouns do not need capital letters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743786Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-899-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Proper nouns need capital letters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743790Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5145-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales can be set in real or fictional places. This traditional tale is set in Japan."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743794Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5145-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Illustrations can be a way to help us to predict and understand the story. We can 'read' the illustrations in a book."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5145-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Predictions can be made based on making connections and pattern seeking."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743802Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5145-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Making links to our own experiences is a way to help to understand the actions of a character."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743806Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5145-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Greed is one of the main themes in 'Yoshi the Stonecutter'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.743810Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-952-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'a' is the most common spelling for the 'o' phoneme after 'w' and 'qu'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-952-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """How to spell the common exception words: other, mother, brother, another and nothing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744195Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-906-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple sentence is about one idea and it makes complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744218Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-906-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple sentence can be written in the present tense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744222Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-906-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple sentence contains one verb and at least one noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744228Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-906-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The verb carries the tense of a sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-906-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences start with capital letters and most often end with full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-976-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe has more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-976-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show possession."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-976-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An 's is used to show belonging after the first noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.744250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-941-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two or more words that sound the same but have different meanings or spellings are called homophones."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-941-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Hear' and 'here' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-941-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Quiet' and 'quite' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745213Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-941-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Night' and 'knight' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745217Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-941-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Buy', 'by' and 'buy' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7175-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vocabulary can be generated and used in different ways using a word bank"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7175-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives describe a noun"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7175-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using two adjectives, a comma is placed in between them, such as 'kind, friendly'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7175-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using adverbs can add detail to how family members do something"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745236Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7175-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two ideas can be joined using a joining word like 'and' to form a compound sentence"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5641-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your imagination can help you to think of things that do not exist in real life."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5641-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A noun is a naming word for people, places or things."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5641-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective is a word that describes a noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745257Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5641-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is easier for the reader to picture the nouns we are writing about if we describe them using an adjective."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745261Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8891-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Characterisation is the way an author describes and develops the characters in a story."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8891-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Appearance is how a character looks on the outside."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745269Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8891-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Personality refers to what a character is like on the inside."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745273Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8891-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Plop is a cute, fluffy barn owl who is clumsy but friendly."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8891-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The author’s characterisation of Plop makes him a likeable character, which is engaging for the reader."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.745280Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-951-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'il' and 'al' representations are usually found in polysyllabic words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-951-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are not many words ending in 'il'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746239Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-951-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Not many nouns end in 'al', but many adjectives do."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746243Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-951-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: father and clothes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746246Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7180-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing a letter is a way to communicate to someone"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746250Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7180-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Letters start with a greeting such as 'Dear Anna' or 'To Anna'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746256Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7180-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Writing in the first person uses words such as 'I', 'me' or 'my'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746260Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7180-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When answering questions, you can include part of the question in the answer to create a full sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746264Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6207-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes from a written plan support in writing and ensure important information is included in an information text."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746268Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6207-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a range of sentence types in our writing helps it to flow."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746272Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6207-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Co-ordination can be used to join two simple sentences that carry equal importance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6207-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Subordination can be used to stretch a main clause and add greater detail."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746280Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6183-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-chronological report is a type of non-fiction text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746284Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6183-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-chronological report provides information on a subject, person or event."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746288Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6183-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are used when making a plan and they are short and only capture key vocabulary and important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746292Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6183-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are not written in full sentences and do not require capital letters, full stops or commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746296Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4750-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters u, y and j all have a lead in and a lead out"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746300Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4750-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters u, y and j all start on the baseline"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4750-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letters y and j have a loop at the bottom of the descender as the lead out line"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4750-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters u and y are similarly formed but the y has a descender"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746311Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6827-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes a noun"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746315Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6827-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives are often put in front of the noun in a sentence, such as 'scared goat'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746319Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6827-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe what a character might look like, such as 'small'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746323Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6827-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives can be used to describe a character's personality, such as 'brave'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746329Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-921-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ay’ is a representation of the ay phoneme that often comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746594Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-921-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘ai’ is a representation of the ay phoneme that often is found in the middle of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746598Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-921-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "‘a-e’ is a representation of the ay phoneme that is often found ‘last but one’."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746602Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-921-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: old, cold and gold."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746606Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-921-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """How to write a complete sentence containing words and spellings previously and recently learnt."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746610Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1020-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe is an important piece of punctuation with more than one purpose."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746616Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1020-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can contract two words together."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746620Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1020-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another singular noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1020-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Apostrophes for contraction and singular possession are useful in writing for different reasons."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-1020-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Apostrophes are most deeply understood when word class is understood."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-917-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Or' is a type of joining word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746637Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-917-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining two simple sentences with 'or' forms a compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746641Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-917-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The second idea offers an option or result of the first idea if 'or' is used to join them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746645Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-917-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each of the two ideas holds equal grammatical weight in the sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-917-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Grammatically accurate sentences start with capital letters and most often end with full stops."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746653Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5439-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Nursery rhymes are a good way to introduce us to rhythms of language, new vocabulary and sentence structures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746657Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5439-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Hickory Dickory Dock' has some rhyming words, such as 'clock', 'tick-tock' and 'Dock'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746661Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5439-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Knowing the tune, words, rhythm and actions of a Nursery Rhyme make it entertaining for whoever is watching."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746665Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5439-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Hickory Dickory Dock' and 'Little Bo Peep' are similar because they both include animals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5439-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personal responses are a way of sharing your own thoughts, feelings, and opinions about a poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746672Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5194-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Children of Lir’ is divided into short chapters and has a beginning, middle and end, like all traditional tales."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746676Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5194-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sounding out using phonics strategies is our most helpful way to decode unfamiliar words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5194-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Searching for a ‘word within a word’ is a useful strategy to comprehend words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5194-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Read to the end of the sentence to help to decide the meaning of an unfamiliar word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5194-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-reading a sentence fluently after decoding helps to make sense of what has been read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7194-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Kit Wright is a poet and is known for writing imaginative poetry for children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746696Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7194-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘The Magic Box’ by Kit Wright is a poem about putting a variety of unique and wonderful items into a special box."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7194-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The poem explores themes including: imagination, magic and wonder, childhood, family and memories."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-7194-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can read with expression to show meaning and emphasise words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.746710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8110-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Opinions are views that a person has about something and can be known as a 'point of view'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8110-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reasons should be used to explain why we have a particular opinion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747374Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8110-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Because' is the joining word that allows you to explain why you have that opinion."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747378Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-950-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The 'll' representation of the 'l' sound is often found after short vowels in single syllable words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-950-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'el' and 'le' representations are usually found in polysyllabic words."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747386Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-950-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'el' spelling is much less common than 'le'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747392Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-950-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The 'el' spelling is often used after 'm', 'n', 'r', 's', 'v' and 'w'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747396Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-950-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: child and children."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747400Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-947-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ce' is sometimes used to represent the 's' phoneme at the end of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747404Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-947-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'se' is sometimes used to represent the 's' phoneme at the end of a word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-947-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception word 'once' and high frequnecy word 'going'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747412Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-922-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "a', 'eigh' and 'ey' are alternative spellings for the 'ay' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-922-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Words in word families often have similar spellings."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747420Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-922-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: told, hold and oh."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747424Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5441-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'The Magic Porridge Pot' has some words in that sound like what it is describing, such as 'split, splat, splot'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5441-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This is called onomatopoeia."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5441-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These words can be spoken and sung with expression and intonation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5441-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Personal responses are a way of sharing your own thoughts, feelings, and opinions about a poem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8919-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Coming to England' is a book based on the true story about Floella Benjamin."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747444Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8919-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Coming to England' is a non-fiction book written and illustrated in the style of a fiction book."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747448Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8919-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Floella Benjamin emigrated from Trinidad to the United Kingdom."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8919-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Similarities and differences can be made about two books with the same theme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8899-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using a range of strategies helps to build our understanding of a text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8899-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Retrieving means finding information directly from the text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747465Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8899-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Searching for clues within the text helps us to infer greater meaning and draw conclusions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747469Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8899-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Having rich discussions improves our understanding and offers opportunities for hearing different ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747474Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8899-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Plop met a Scout who told him about why he thinks night time is ‘fun’."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27603-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful listening includes looking at the person speaking and paying close attention."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27603-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Successful speaking includes speaking loudly and clearly enough for everyone to hear."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27603-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questions are sentences which ask something and require an answer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27603-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When answering questions, the response should be about the question."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-27603-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Speaking in full sentences helps the listener understand what is being said."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8920-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A fact is a statement of truth."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747744Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8920-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'Coming to England' is about Floella Benjamin's life so it can be used to learn information and facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747748Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8920-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two facts can be joined together using the joining word 'and'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747752Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8920-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two complete ideas can become one sentence by placing 'and' in between them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8920-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A proper noun is a type of noun that needs a capital letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.747765Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8901-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a story helps us to consider themes or big ideas told through the plot"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8901-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character's feelings and emotions change depending on what they are doing or what challenges they may be facing"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748076Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8901-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some adjectives describe feelings and emotions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748080Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8901-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Linking our own experiences to what we are reading helps us to understand the characters' feelings and actions"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8901-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Resilience means never giving up and keeping trying even when things may be difficult"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748089Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-924-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'ee' and 'ea' are common spellings of the 'ee' phoneme."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-924-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """'e-e' is a representation of the 'ee' phoneme that is often found 'last but one'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748097Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-924-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words 'find', 'kind', 'mind' and 'behind'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748102Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8835-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A person's actions and words can tell us about their character."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748107Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8835-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Emmeline Pankhurst showed determination and bravery in pursuit of fighting for women's rights."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8835-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Emmeline Pankhurst showed resilience and never gave up."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8835-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Emmeline Pankhurst influenced many others through her actions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748118Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8835-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Emmeline Pankhurst contributed to significant historical change."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748122Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5410-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The contents page can help direct you to a particular topic, such as 'feeding'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748126Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5410-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Non-fiction books have photographs, captions and headings to make the information easier to understand."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5410-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Non-fiction books teach information about a topic, such as how to care for a cat or kitten."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748134Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5410-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Re-listening to or re-reading a page from a non-fiction book helps to retain and recall facts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6167-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The purpose of the build-up is to develop the plot/characters, introduce a problem and build up tension and excitement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748142Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6167-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain ambitious vocabulary."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748146Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6167-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Our plan will contain nouns, adjectives, verbs and adverbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748152Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6167-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using ambitious vocabulary helps to paint a vivid picture in the reader’s mind and make writing exciting to read."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5193-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales are stories that are retold again and again and can be retold in different ways."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748160Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5193-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales can be set in real or fictional places."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748164Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5193-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some traditional tales have magical aspects such as magical potions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5193-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Lots of traditional tales involve talking animals or characters being turned into animals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5193-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Traditional tales often have heroes and villains. The villain is the stepmother."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-940-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Two or more words that sound the same but have different meanings or spellings are called homophones."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748655Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-940-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'There', 'their' and 'they're' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-940-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'To', 'too' and 'two' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748664Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-940-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Won' and 'one' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748668Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-940-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Our', 'hour' and 'are' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748672Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-954-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘aw’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that often comes at the end of a word and sometimes in the middle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748676Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-954-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """‘oor’ is a representation of the 'or' phoneme that sometimes comes at the end of a word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-954-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "'Paw' and 'poor' are homophones."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-954-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "How to spell the common exception words: people, Mr and Mrs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4786-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A capital letter is the upper case formation of a letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4786-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The letters B, D, P, R, I, E, F and L all start on the ascender line."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748696Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4786-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The capital letters B, D, P, R and L are formed by one continuous movement and you do not need to lift your pencil."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4786-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letters B, D, P and R all make a vertical line down, go back up and around in a clockwise direction."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-4786-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The letters I, E and F need the pencil to be lifted to form the horizontal lines."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748707Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6185-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-chronological report is a type of non-fiction text."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6185-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A non-chronological report provides information on a subject, person or event."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6185-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are used when making a plan and they are short and only capture key vocabulary and important information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748719Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6185-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Notes are not written in full sentences and do not require capital letters, full stops or commas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6176-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An opening will introduce the setting and main characters."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748745Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6176-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A descriptive opening will contain expanded noun phrases."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6176-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A descriptive opening will contain adverbs and verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6176-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use notes from our plan to form full sentences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8927-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A postcard is written to someone when you are away somewhere, in this case Paddington in London."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748760Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8927-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Postcards are written in the first person, using 'I', 'me' or 'my'."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8927-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adding descriptive language about places and feelings can help the person reading it imagine the experience."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748770Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8927-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A postcard needs to start with a greeting to who you are writing to, using 'Dear ...' or 'To ...'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748776Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-8927-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A list of places you have seen can be included in a postcard, with a comma in between and 'and' before the final place."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29014-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe a character's personality, such as 'cunning' wolf."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748785Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29014-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe a character's appearance, such as 'furry' wolf."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748788Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29014-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When you use two adjectives to describe a noun, you need to separate them with a comma."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748792Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29014-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two ideas can be joined together using 'and' to form one compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748796Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29014-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In a compound sentence, each idea must make complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-913-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are four types of simple sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-913-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Any simple sentence is a sentence about one idea that makes complete sense."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748943Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-913-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each type of simple sentence has a different purpose for the reader."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748947Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-913-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A statement often ends with a full stop, a question with a question mark and a command can end with an exclamation mark."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748951Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-913-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A command starts with an imperative verb."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6212-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A recount will involve you describing events and experiences in detail."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6212-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An expanded noun phrase is a group of words with no verb that adds detail to a noun."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748965Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6212-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Expanded noun phrases contain two adjectives, separated by a comma."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748969Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6212-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When we write a plan, we use notes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748973Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29019-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Traditional tales often have repeated elements, making them easier to remember and retell."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29019-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The repeated element of ‘The Three Little Pigs’ is each pig building their house to have it blown down by the wolf."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29019-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The pig building the house and the wolf blowing it down are two ideas that are related, so can be joined using  ‘and’."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748985Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29019-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe things and characters, such as the houses and the wolf."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-29019-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When using more than one adjective to describe a noun, they must be separated with a comma."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.748995Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5481-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sequencing language can be used at the start of a sentence, such as 'Suddenly,'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749556Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5481-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The middle of a story introduces the main plot and problem, such as the porridge overflowing"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5481-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rehearsing a sentence out loud before writing it helps us to remember it"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749563Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5481-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Reading a sentence back after writing helps to check it makes sense"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749567Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5481-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using an exclamation mark at the end shows shock or excitement"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5648-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A non-chronological report must be written in a formal tone, avoiding language choices associated with fiction writing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749575Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5648-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Contractions are not used in formal writing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5648-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Information can be shared with the reader by phrasing it as a question."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6174-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A setting is where the story takes place."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749586Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6174-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "We can use our senses to describe a setting in detail."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749590Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6174-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An expanded noun phrase can contain two adjectives to describe a noun, separated by a comma."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749594Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6174-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A character’s appearance is what they look like."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749598Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6174-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A character’s personality is what kind of person they are on the inside and how they behave."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749602Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6200-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The first section of the report will be all about bats."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749606Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6200-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe can show if a noun belongs to another singular noun."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749614Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6200-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Apostrophes for singular possession are useful to make our writing clear."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749618Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6200-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An apostrophe sits at the same height as the ascender of a letter."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749622Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5644-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Instructions use numbers and ordering fronted adverbials to add order and sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5644-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions can contain adjectives to describe the nouns."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5644-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Instructions contain imperative verbs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.749633Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-20074-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An adjective or list of adjectives can describe a noun, such as 'sweet mango' or 'noisy, chirping birds'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750133Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-20074-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Describing a setting using senses helps the reader to imagine they are there or have been there."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750139Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-20074-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The joining word 'and' can be used to join two complete ideas into a full sentence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750144Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-20074-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Joining two simple sentences with the joining word 'and' is a compound sentence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750147Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6184-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A viewpoint is how you see or feel about something."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750152Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6184-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Viewpoint fronted adverbials are sentence starters that share the writer’s view on something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750155Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6184-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All fronted adverbials start with capital letters and have a comma after."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750159Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6184-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This section of the report contains interesting facts about Florence Nightingale's life."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750163Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6184-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sentences should be said aloud before writing to ensure they make sense and read back once written to check for errors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750167Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-975-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In contractions, the apostrophe shows where a letter or letters would be if the words were written in full."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750171Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-975-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Saying the expanded form of a contraction can help to identify where the apostrophe goes and how to spell it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750176Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-970-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A suffix is a letter or group of letters at the end of a word which creates another word."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-970-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding '-er' creates an extra syllable to the word."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-970-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the adjective ends in two consonant letters, the ending is simply added on."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-970-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'y', the 'y' is changed to 'i' before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-970-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the root word ends in a consonant + 'e', the 'e' is removed before the suffix is added."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5477-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Retelling a story helps to remember the main events and use storytelling language, such as 'Once upon a time,'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750409Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5477-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Story mountains map out the beginning, middle and end"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750413Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5477-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Only the most important events in the story need to be on a story mountain"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750417Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5477-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using sequencing language such as 'The next day,' at the start of the sentence helps the reader follow the story"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750421Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-5477-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding descriptive language will help when the story is being written"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6826-1
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An adjective describes a noun"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6826-2
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using descriptions with adjectives makes writing more interesting"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750433Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6826-3
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives are often put in front of the noun in a sentence, such as 'a mean troll'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750437Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6826-4
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Adjectives can be used to describe what a character might look like, such as 'huge'"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750440Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:keylearningpoint-lesson-6826-5
  a oakcurric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adjectives can also describe a character's personality, such as 'selfish'"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.750446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

